Key Match Events: DL Hall worked 7 scoreless innings in the best start of his career
Willy Adames and Rhys Hoskins each homered and drove in three runs
Milwaukee Brewers scored 10 runs in the 9th inning to win 14-0
Miscellaneous Highlights: Milwaukee Brewers stole four bases, two by Brice Turang
Others: The game was the second of a doubleheader, with the first game ending in a 5-4 win for the Brewers in 10 innings
